# ML Engineering — {{companyName}}

## When to Use
- Building end-to-end ML pipelines (training → serving)
- Deploying models to production (batch or real-time)
- Implementing forecasting, recommendation, or classification systems

## Pipeline Patterns
- **Feature engineering** — Reproducible transformations with feature stores
- **Training** — Distributed training, hyperparameter optimization
- **Evaluation** — Automated model validation against holdout sets
- **Serving** — REST/gRPC endpoints, batch inference, edge deployment
- **Monitoring** — Data drift, prediction drift, latency tracking

## Deployment Strategies
- Blue-green deployments for model updates
- Shadow mode for new models alongside production
- Canary releases with gradual traffic shifting
- Rollback procedures with model version pinning

## Best Practices
- Automate the full train → evaluate → deploy pipeline
- Use containerized inference for reproducibility
- Implement circuit breakers for model endpoint failures
- Log predictions for auditing and retraining
